Blocks.childText: HYMNS OF DEVOTION. ENTREATY. 6s & 5s. D. E. G. MONK (1819 1. In the hour of tri - al, Je-sus,plead for me; Lest by base de - ni - al I de-part from Thee; popp 0.2 fo/ When Thou see'st me wav-er, With a look re - call, Nor for fear or fa- vor Suf-fer me to fall. 9: 92 In the Hour of Trial. 4 When my last hour cometh, 1 In the hour of trial, Fraught with strife and pain, Jesus, plead for me; When my dust returneth Lest by base denial To the dust again; I depart from Thee; On Thy truth relying, When Thou see'st me waver, Through that mortal strife, With a look recall, Jesus, take me, dying, Nor for fear or favor To eternal life. Suffer me to fall. James Montgomery (1771- 1854). 2 With forbidden pleasures 93 2 Cor. xii: 9. (TUNE VIRGO.) Would this vain world charm; 1 Let me but hear my Saviour say, Or its sordid treasures "Strength shall be equal to thy day;" Spread to work me harm; Then I rejoice in deep distress, Bring to my remembrance Leaning on all-sufficient grace. Sad Gethsemane, Or, in darker semblance, Cross-crown'd Calvary. 2 I can do all things- or can bear All suffering, if my Lord be there; 3 Should Thy mercy send me Sweet pleasures mingle with the pains, Sorrow, toil; and woe; While He my sinking head sustains. Or should pain attend me On my path below; 3 I glory in infirmity, Grant that I may never That Christ's own power may rest on me; Fail Thy hand to see; When I am weak, then am I strong; Grant that I may ever Grace is my shield, and Christ my song. Cast my care on Thee. Rev. Isaac Watts (1674 - 1748). (38)
